   band atmospheric transparency in the window around 350 mu m wavelength.
   The tippers were deployed on Maunakea, Hawaii, at the South Pole, and in
   the vicinity of Cerro Chajnantor in northern Chile. Identical
   instruments permit direct comparison of these sites. Observing
   conditions at the South Pole and in the Chajnantor area are better than
   on Maunakea. Simultaneous measurements with two tippers demonstrate
   conditions at the summit of Cerro Chajnantor are significantly better
   than on the Chajnantor plateau.}},
